data.enText: easy to see or notice; clear or definite

data.chText: 这种作用在年轻一些的病人身上尤为明显。
data.enText: This effect is particularly noticeable in younger patients.

data.chText: 很明显这一家没有人在场。
data.enText: It was noticeable that none of the family were present.

data.chText: 女孩子的分数明显地高于男孩子。
data.enText: Marks were noticeably higher for girls than for boys.

tr: capable or worthy of being perceived
example: noticeable for its vivid historical background
the obtrusive behavior of a spoiled child
after a noticeable pause the lecturer continued

value.def: Something that is noticeable is very obvious, so that it is easy to see, hear, or recognize.

example.ex: It is noticeable that women do not have the rivalry that men have...
example.tran: 显而易见，女性不像男人们那样好勇斗狠。

example.ex: The most noticeable effect of these changes is in the way people are now working together.
example.tran: 这些变化带来的最明显效果体现在人们现在一起工作的方式上。

value.tran: 容易注意到的;显著的;明显的

example.ex: Standards of living were deteriorating rather noticeably...
example.tran: 生活水平下降得十分明显。

example.ex: There are also many physical signs, most noticeably a change in facial features.
example.tran: 还有很多体貌特征，最明显的是面容的变化。
